# 2. 見返してやる

Ena: <*Yawn*... So sleepy...>
Mizuki: <Man, the sun's so bright...!>
Ena: <Keep it down, Amia. It's like you're yelling right into my ear.>
Mizuki: <Why? You and I are the only ones here anyway, Enanan.>
Ena: <And I'm telling you to pipe down!>
Ena: <*Sigh*... I think I'll log off now. There's only a few minor adjustments left to make so...>
Mizuki: <Then I'll log off after I get a look at it♪>
Ena: <No way. Not until it's completely done.>
Mizuki: <Aww, not even just a tiny little peek? It'll help me with the video if I know what sort of imagery I should be focusing on too, you know?>
Ena: <You say that, but I know you just want to look at it...>
Ena: <Come to think of it, Yuki left at her usual time, but K left pretty early today. I wonder if she had something to do?>
Mizuki: <Oh, she said it's her day to go to the hospital.>
Ena: <Oh, right... She can only visit during the day.>
Mizuki: <Why don't you get some sunshine for a change too, Enanan?>
Ena: <I am, aren't I?>
Mizuki: <No, by actually going outside. You never know, it might feel good.>
Ena: <You're one to talk. Plus, aren't you about to go to bed?>
Mizuki: <Yup♪ Staying up late is bad for the skin so...>
Mizuki: <So I think I'll leave things here. Later, Enanan.>
Ena: <Okay, good night.>
Ena: I'll brush my teeth and go to bed too then...
Akito: Morning...
Ena: Morning.
Akito: You stayed up all night again?
Ena: And what if I did? Just go to school already, will you?
Akito: I doubt a night school student would know, but I still have plenty of time.
Ena: Oh? Thanks for the tip, not like I care or anything.
Ena: Huh? What's this?
Akito: Oh, they're some art exhibit flyers dad brought home. It's just never-ending with him.
Ena: I know, right? They just keep piling up, so I wish he'd stop bringing them home.
Ena: Wait... This piece is by that artist I like...
Ena: Shibuya Art Contest... This person won last time.
Ena: (Sigh... It must be nice to win something like this...)
Ena: (And this contest is a pretty serious one at that, so I can't possibly...)
???: Do you want to enter in the contest?
Ena: What...?
Ena: Wh-What's it to you...? It's my choice, isn't it?
Dad: Yes, it is.
Dad: But this contest attracts artists that are as good as actual professionals every year.
Dad: So you don't stand a chance.
Ena: What...?! Oh, I get it. I'm too talentless or not worthy of entering into this contest, aren't I?
Dad: That's not what I'm saying. I just think it'll be difficult to win any of the prizes.
Dad: But if that doesn't bother you, then go right on ahead.
Ena: Ugh...
Akito: H-Hey...!
Ena: (Won't stand a chance? Can't win anything? What if I can? I won't know unless I try, right?!)
Ena: (I've never entered into any big contests like this before, so I have no idea what's going to happen...)
Ena: (But I'm sure to get recognition if I win something!)
Ena: (Even from him...!)
Ena: That's it... I'm gonna win it all in this contest!
Ena: And the paint is... Oh, here.
Ena: (I know that I decided to make a submission for this contest, but going out to buy supplies after an all-nighter feels...)
Ena: (No, I don't really have a choice. My old paint is all dried up after not being used for so long.)
Kanade: Ena...?
Ena: Oh, Kanade! What are you doing here?
Kanade: I was visiting my father. How about you?
Ena: I... Um... I was getting art supplies.
Kanade: Art supplies?
Kanade: Wow, you're entering into a contest?
Ena: Yeah, it's a pretty big one too. Some of the other artists are practically pros too.
Kanade: Really? That sounds cool.
Ena: Well, anyone can submit a piece so it's really nothing...
Kanade: Ena?
Ena: Oh, I'm sorry. It's just that... I've never been in a contest like this before so I'm just a little worried is all...
Kanade: You're worried?
Ena: Yeah, I mean... I'm wondering if I can do a good job.
Kanade: ...
Kanade: I don't know much about actual art, but I can tell you this at least...
Kanade: I like your art, Ena.
Kanade: So please give it your best shot.
Ena: Thank you, Kanade.
Ena: I'll do what I can.
Ena: I'm home... Oh, right. There's no one here.
Ena: Hehe. But I'm happy that I ran into Kanade today.
Kanade: I like your art, Ena.
Ena: Time to get started!
Ena: (And I'll put a shadow in here... There. Looks good!)
Ena: (But...)
Ena: (This motif sort of loses its impact...)
Ena: (I've heard that ambiguity or blurring things on purpose actually loses you points so...)
Ena: (That means I should...)
Ena: Right, one more try. I still have time.
Ena: No...!
Ena: This isn't right. It needs to stand out from the rest of the piece more...
Ena: (It needs to be seen by everyone... It needs to be recognized...!)
